import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='year', y='people', data=data, color='blue')
    chart.axhline(y=data['people'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the trend of population growth over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='age', kde=False, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['age'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Median age: {:.2f}'.format(data['age'].median()))
    plt.xlabel('Age')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of age in the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['sex', 'people']].groupby('sex').sum().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='sex', y='people', data=data, palette='Set2')
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution of the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Gender')
    plt.ylabel('Number of People')
    plt.xticks([0, 1], ['Male', 'Female'])
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x=data['people'])
    ax.axvline(data['people'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of people in the population?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Number of People')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['age', 'people']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='age', y='people', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between age and number of people in the population?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
